If `WalletInitInterface` is an interface class, maybe we can have an interface without method definitions. Have you considered an interface with pure virtual functions?

```c++
    /** Get wallet help string */
    virtual std::string GetWalletHelpString(bool showDebug) = 0;
    /** Check wallet parameter interaction */
    virtual bool WalletParameterInteraction() = 0;
    /** Register wallet RPC*/
    virtual void RegisterWalletRPC(CRPCTable &) = 0;
    /** Verify wallets */
    virtual bool VerifyWallets() = 0;
    /** Open wallets*/
    virtual bool OpenWallets() = 0;
    /** Start wallets*/
    virtual void StartWallets(CScheduler& scheduler) = 0;
    /** Flush Wallets*/
    virtual void FlushWallets() = 0;
    /** Stop Wallets*/
    virtual void StopWallets() = 0;
    /** Close wallets */
    virtual void CloseWallets() = 0;
